The farmer&#8217;s body was found yesterday by his son on the kitchen floor with gunshot wounds. JOHANNESBURG Police have launched a manhunt for a group of suspects after a 54-year-old farmer was found murdered at Spitskop small holding outside Thabazimbi. The farmer s body was found yesterday by his son on the kitchen floor with gunshot wounds. Police say the deceased's vehicle was discovered abandoned some kilometres from the crime scene.Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says no arrests have been made and has urged community members to come forward with information that may lead to the arrest of the suspects. The police have launched a manhunt on suspects who attacked the 54-year-old. It s not clear what was stolen but the investigation continues. 